Preheat oven to 375 degrees F. In a large bowl, combine pepperoni, ham, green pepper, mushrooms, onion, cheese, pizza sauce, garlic, oregano, basil and chilies. In another bowl, beat eggs, blend in milk and canola oil; mix into pizza mixture. Combine flour and baking powder and mix into pizza mixture until well blended. Spoon into non-stick muffin tins. Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned. Serve warm or cold. Store in the refrigerator or freezer.